  <Name>k__BackingField: 1 John
  fancyName: 
  nickname: 1jn
  language: English
  lang: eng
  version: New Living Translation
  ver: NLT
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Introduction
      content: 'We proclaim to you the one who existed from the beginning,[COMMENT[0]]
        whom we have heard and seen. We saw him with our own eyes and touched him
        with our own hands. He is the Word of life. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: What was from the beginning.
    - title: 
      content: 'This one who is life itself was revealed to us, and we have seen
        him. And now we testify and proclaim to you that he is the one who is eternal
        life. He was with the Father, and then he was revealed to us. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We proclaim to you what we ourselves have actually seen and heard
        so that you may have fellowship with us. And our fellowship is with the Father
        and with his Son, Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are writing these things so that you may fully share our joy.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'so that our joy may be complete; '
        - ft: 'some manuscripts read '
          body: your joy.
    - title: Living in the Light
      content: 'This is the message we heard from Jesus[COMMENT[0]] and now declare
        to you: God is light, and there is no darkness in him at all. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: from him.
    - title: 
      content: 'So we are lying if we say we have fellowship with God but go on living
        in spiritual darkness; we are not practicing the truth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if we are living in the light, as God is in the light, then we
        have fellowship with each other, and the blood of Jesus, his Son, cleanses
        us from all sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If we claim we have no sin, we are only fooling ourselves and not
        living in the truth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if we confess our sins to him, he is faithful and just to forgive
        us our sins and to cleanse us from all wickedness. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: If we claim we have not sinned, we are calling God a liar and showing
        that his word has no place in our hearts.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'My dear children, I am writing this to you so that you will not sin.
        But if anyone does sin, we have an advocate who pleads our case before the
        Father. He is Jesus Christ, the one who is truly righteous. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He himself is the sacrifice that atones for our sins\u2014and not
        only our sins but the sins of all the world.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And we can be sure that we know him if we obey his commandments. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If someone claims, \u201CI know God,\u201D but doesn\u2019t obey
        God\u2019s commandments, that person is a liar and is not living in the truth. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But those who obey God\u2019s word truly show how completely they
        love him. That is how we know we are living in him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who say they live in God should live their lives as Jesus did.  '
      comments: []
    - title: A New Commandment
      content: "Dear friends, I am not writing a new commandment for you; rather
        it is an old one you have had from the very beginning. This old commandment\u2014to
        love one another\u2014is the same message you heard before. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet it is also new. Jesus lived the truth of this commandment, and
        you also are living it. For the darkness is disappearing, and the true light
        is already shining.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If anyone claims, \u201CI am living in the light,\u201D but hates
        a fellow believer,[COMMENT[0]] that person is still living in darkness. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'hates his brother; '
        - ft: also in 2:11.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Anyone who loves a fellow believer[COMMENT[0]] is living in the light
        and does not cause others to stumble. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: loves his brother.
    - title: 
      content: 'But anyone who hates a fellow believer is still living and walking
        in darkness. Such a person does not know the way to go, having been blinded
        by the darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am writing to you who are God\u2019s children\n\tbecause your sins
        have been forgiven through Jesus.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: through his name.
    - title: 
      content: "I am writing to you who are mature in the faith[COMMENT[0]]because
        you know Christ, who existed from the beginning.\n\tI am writing to you who
        are young in the faith\n\tbecause you have won your battle with the evil
        one.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'to you fathers; '
        - ft: also in 2:14.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I have written to you who are God\u2019s children\n\tbecause you
        know the Father.\n\tI have written to you who are mature in the faith\n\tbecause
        you know Christ, who existed from the beginning.\n\tI have written to you
        who are young in the faith\n\tbecause you are strong.\n\tGod\u2019s word
        lives in your hearts,\n\tand you have won your battle with the evil one.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Do Not Love This World
      content: 'Do not love this world nor the things it offers you, for when you
        love the world, you do not have the love of the Father in you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the world offers only a craving for physical pleasure, a craving
        for everything we see, and pride in our achievements and possessions. These
        are not from the Father, but are from this world. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And this world is fading away, along with everything that people
        crave. But anyone who does what pleases God will live forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Warning about Antichrists
      content: 'Dear children, the last hour is here. You have heard that the Antichrist
        is coming, and already many such antichrists have appeared. From this we
        know that the last hour has come. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These people left our churches, but they never really belonged with
        us; otherwise they would have stayed with us. When they left, it proved that
        they did not belong with us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you are not like that, for the Holy One has given you his Spirit,[COMMENT[0]]
        and all of you know the truth. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: But you have an anointing from the Holy One.
    - title: 
      content: "So I am writing to you not because you don\u2019t know the truth
        but because you know the difference between truth and lies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And who is a liar? Anyone who says that Jesus is not the Christ.[COMMENT[0]]
        Anyone who denies the Father and the Son is an antichrist.[COMMENT[1]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:22a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: not the Messiah.
      - number: '2:22b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: the antichrist.
    - title: 
      content: "Anyone who denies the Son doesn\u2019t have the Father, either. But
        anyone who acknowledges the Son has the Father also.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So you must remain faithful to what you have been taught from the
        beginning. If you do, you will remain in fellowship with the Son and with
        the Father. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And in this fellowship we enjoy the eternal life he promised us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am writing these things to warn you about those who want to lead
        you astray. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you have received the Holy Spirit,[COMMENT[0]] and he lives within
        you, so you don\u2019t need anyone to teach you what is true. For the Spirit[COMMENT[1]]
        teaches you everything you need to know, and what he teaches is true\u2014it
        is not a lie. So just as he has taught you, remain in fellowship with Christ.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:27a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: the anointing from him.
      - number: '2:27b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: the anointing.
    - title: Living as Children of God
      content: 'And now, dear children, remain in fellowship with Christ so that
        when he returns, you will be full of courage and not shrink back from him
        in shame.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Since we know that Christ is righteous, we also know that all who
        do what is right are God\u2019s children."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "See how very much our Father loves us, for he calls us his children,
        and that is what we are! But the people who belong to this world don\u2019t
        recognize that we are God\u2019s children because they don\u2019t know him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Dear friends, we are already God\u2019s children, but he has not
        yet shown us what we will be like when Christ appears. But we do know that
        we will be like him, for we will see him as he really is. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And all who have this eager expectation will keep themselves pure,
        just as he is pure.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Everyone who sins is breaking God\u2019s law, for all sin is contrary
        to the law of God. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And you know that Jesus came to take away our sins, and there is
        no sin in him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Anyone who continues to live in him will not sin. But anyone who
        keeps on sinning does not know him or understand who he is.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Dear children, don\u2019t let anyone deceive you about this: When
        people do what is right, it shows that they are righteous, even as Christ
        is righteous. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But when people keep on sinning, it shows that they belong to the
        devil, who has been sinning since the beginning. But the Son of God came
        to destroy the works of the devil. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who have been born into God\u2019s family do not make a practice
        of sinning, because God\u2019s life[COMMENT[0]] is in them. So they can\u2019t
        keep on sinning, because they are children of God. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: because his seed.
    - title: 
      content: 'So now we can tell who are children of God and who are children of
        the devil. Anyone who does not live righteously and does not love other believers[COMMENT[0]]
        does not belong to God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: does not love his brother.
    - title: Love One Another
      content: 'This is the message you have heard from the beginning: We should
        love one another. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We must not be like Cain, who belonged to the evil one and killed
        his brother. And why did he kill him? Because Cain had been doing what was
        evil, and his brother had been doing what was righteous. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So don\u2019t be surprised, dear brothers and sisters,[COMMENT[0]]
        if the world hates you.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: brothers.
    - title: 
      content: 'If we love our brothers and sisters who are believers,[COMMENT[0]]
        it proves that we have passed from death to life. But a person who has no
        love is still dead. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'the brothers; '
        - ft: similarly in 3:16.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Anyone who hates another brother or sister[COMMENT[0]] is really
        a murderer at heart. And you know that murderers don\u2019t have eternal
        life within them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: hates his brother.
    - title: 
      content: 'We know what real love is because Jesus gave up his life for us.
        So we also ought to give up our lives for our brothers and sisters. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If someone has enough money to live well and sees a brother or sister[COMMENT[0]]
        in need but shows no compassion\u2014how can God\u2019s love be in that person?  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: sees his brother.
    - title: 
      content: "Dear children, let\u2019s not merely say that we love each other;
        let us show the truth by our actions. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our actions will show that we belong to the truth, so we will be
        confident when we stand before God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even if we feel guilty, God is greater than our feelings, and he
        knows everything.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Dear friends, if we don\u2019t feel guilty, we can come to God with
        bold confidence. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And we will receive from him whatever we ask because we obey him
        and do the things that please him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And this is his commandment: We must believe in the name of his Son,
        Jesus Christ, and love one another, just as he commanded us. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who obey God\u2019s commandments remain in fellowship with
        him, and he with them. And we know he lives in us because the Spirit he gave
        us lives in us."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Discerning False Prophets
      content: 'Dear friends, do not believe everyone who claims to speak by the
        Spirit. You must test them to see if the spirit they have comes from God.
        For there are many false prophets in the world. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is how we know if they have the Spirit of God: If a person claiming
        to be a prophet[COMMENT[0]] acknowledges that Jesus Christ came in a real
        body, that person has the Spirit of God. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'If a spirit; '
        - ft: similarly in 4:3.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'But if someone claims to be a prophet and does not acknowledge the
        truth about Jesus, that person is not from God. Such a person has the spirit
        of the Antichrist, which you heard is coming into the world and indeed is
        already here.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you belong to God, my dear children. You have already won a victory
        over those people, because the Spirit who lives in you is greater than the
        spirit who lives in the world. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those people belong to this world, so they speak from the world\u2019s
        viewpoint, and the world listens to them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But we belong to God, and those who know God listen to us. If they
        do not belong to God, they do not listen to us. That is how we know if someone
        has the Spirit of truth or the spirit of deception.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Loving One Another
      content: 'Dear friends, let us continue to love one another, for love comes
        from God. Anyone who loves is a child of God and knows God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But anyone who does not love does not know God, for God is love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God showed how much he loved us by sending his one and only Son into
        the world so that we might have eternal life through him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is real love\u2014not that we loved God, but that he loved us
        and sent his Son as a sacrifice to take away our sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Dear friends, since God loved us that much, we surely ought to love
        each other. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No one has ever seen God. But if we love each other, God lives in
        us, and his love is brought to full expression in us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And God has given us his Spirit as proof that we live in him and
        he in us. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Furthermore, we have seen with our own eyes and now testify that
        the Father sent his Son to be the Savior of the world. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All who declare that Jesus is the Son of God have God living in them,
        and they live in God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We know how much God loves us, and we have put our trust in his love.\n\tGod
        is love, and all who live in love live in God, and God lives in them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And as we live in God, our love grows more perfect. So we will not
        be afraid on the day of judgment, but we can face him with confidence because
        we live like Jesus here in this world.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Such love has no fear, because perfect love expels all fear. If we
        are afraid, it is for fear of punishment, and this shows that we have not
        fully experienced his perfect love. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We love each other[COMMENT[0]] because he loved us first.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'We love. '
        - ft: 'Other manuscripts read '
          body: 'We love God; '
        - ft: 'still others read '
          body: We love him.
    - title: 
      content: "If someone says, \u201CI love God,\u201D but hates a fellow believer,[COMMENT[0]]
        that person is a liar; for if we don\u2019t love people we can see, how can
        we love God, whom we cannot see? "
      comments:
      - number: '4:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: hates his brother.
    - title: 
      content: 'And he has given us this command: Those who love God must also love
        their fellow believers.[COMMENT[0]]'
      comments:
      - number: '4:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: The one who loves God must also love his brother.
  - verses:
    - title: Faith in the Son of God
      content: 'Everyone who believes that Jesus is the Christ[COMMENT[0]] has become
        a child of God. And everyone who loves the Father loves his children, too. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: the Messiah.
    - title: 
      content: "We know we love God\u2019s children if we love God and obey his commandments. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Loving God means keeping his commandments, and his commandments are
        not burdensome. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For every child of God defeats this evil world, and we achieve this
        victory through our faith. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And who can win this battle against the world? Only those who believe
        that Jesus is the Son of God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And Jesus Christ was revealed as God\u2019s Son by his baptism in
        water and by shedding his blood on the cross[COMMENT[0]]\u2014not by water
        only, but by water and blood. And the Spirit, who is truth, confirms it with
        his testimony. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: This is he who came by water and blood.
    - title: 
      content: "So we have these three witnesses[COMMENT[0]]\u2014 "
      comments:
      - number: '5:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'A few very late manuscripts add '
          body: "in heaven\u2014the Father, the Word, and the Holy Spirit, and these
            three are one. And we have three witnesses on earth."
    - title: 
      content: "the Spirit, the water, and the blood\u2014and all three agree. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Since we believe human testimony, surely we can believe the greater
        testimony that comes from God. And God has testified about his Son. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All who believe in the Son of God know in their hearts that this
        testimony is true. Those who don\u2019t believe this are actually calling
        God a liar because they don\u2019t believe what God has testified about his
        Son.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And this is what God has testified: He has given us eternal life,
        and this life is in his Son. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Whoever has the Son has life; whoever does not have God\u2019s Son
        does not have life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Conclusion
      content: 'I have written this to you who believe in the name of the Son of
        God, so that you may know you have eternal life. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And we are confident that he hears us whenever we ask for anything
        that pleases him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And since we know he hears us when we make our requests, we also
        know that he will give us what we ask for.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you see a fellow believer[COMMENT[0]] sinning in a way that does
        not lead to death, you should pray, and God will give that person life. But
        there is a sin that leads to death, and I am not saying you should pray for
        those who commit it. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: a brother.
    - title: 
      content: 'All wicked actions are sin, but not every sin leads to death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We know that God\u2019s children do not make a practice of sinning,
        for God\u2019s Son holds them securely, and the evil one cannot touch them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We know that we are children of God and that the world around us
        is under the control of the evil one.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And we know that the Son of God has come, and he has given us understanding
        so that we can know the true God.[COMMENT[0]] And now we live in fellowship
        with the true God because we live in fellowship with his Son, Jesus Christ.
        He is the only true God, and he is eternal life.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: the one who is true.
    - title: 
      content: "Dear children, keep away from anything that might take God\u2019s
        place in your hearts.[COMMENT[0]]"
      comments:
      - number: '5:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: keep yourselves from idols.
